# App Publish and IIS Deploy

## Staging and IIS Install Paths

| Item | Path |
|------|------|
| Staging share base | `\\<server>\DedgeCommon\Software\DedgeWinApps\<AppName>` |
| IIS install path | `$env:OptPath\DedgeWinApps\<AppName>` |

All ASP.NET Core apps run as IIS virtual applications under `Default Web Site` on port 80.

## Publish: Single App

Each app has its own `Build-And-Publish.ps1`. It publishes to the staging share using `WebApp-FileSystem.pubxml`.

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "<repo-root>\Build-And-Publish.ps1"
```

Version bumps are Patch by default.

## IIS Deploy: Single App

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "<DevTools>\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-DeployApp.ps1" -SiteName <AppName>
```

## IIS Deploy: All Apps

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "<DevTools>\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-RedeployAll.ps1"
```

## Full Deploy Sequence (Publish + Install All)

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "<repo-root>\Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1"
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "<DevTools>\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-RedeployAll.ps1"
```

## Impact Rules

| Change | Action |
|--------|--------|
| Shared client library changed | Rebuild ALL consumer apps, then `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1` |
| Single app changed | Rebuild that app only, then `IIS-DeployApp.ps1 -SiteName <name>` |
| Deploy templates changed | Run `IIS-DeployApp\_deploy.ps1` to sync to servers, then `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1` |

## Post-Deploy Verification

After deploying, run a screenshot/health check tool to verify apps are running.
